      "name": "Hemolysis bench comparison — relative hemolysis index RH",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) was compared against bench plasma-free haemoglobin measurements at five flow-speed operating points. Predicted NIH values fell within ±18% of measured values at all points. The relative hemolysis index RH remained below 1.0 for all candidate configurations, satisfying the COU acceptance criterion. Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic pump geometry to maximise relevance to the submission device.",
