      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity — SST k-omega vs realizable k-epsilon",
      "description": "Two turbulence closure models (SST k-omega and realizable k-epsilon) were applied to the nominal geometry at the design operating point. Predicted NIH differed by 7.3%, which is within the accepted model-form uncertainty band for hemolysis CFD at MRL 2. SST k-omega was selected as the primary model based on superior near-wall resolution and published benchmark performance on rotating machinery."
