    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. Mesh independence (GCI < 2.1%), solver verification (p_obs = 1.97), hemolysis bench comparison (NIH within ±18%), turbulence model sensitivity (7.3% variation within accepted band), and output comparison (RH < 1.0 at all operating points) collectively provide sufficient credibility evidence for the COU. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB submission device.",
